Cephaelis ipecacuanha

   [4414.jpg]
    Authority   (Brot.) Tussac
      Family
     Synonyms   Psychotria ipecacuanha (Brot.) Stokes
   Common names ipecac
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4414

   Notes
   SOURCES (C. ipecacuanha (Stokes) Baill.)
   Williams C 1979a pp 80 [DRA, FER]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 285 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 11 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 451 [USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial herb or shrub. Roots can be harvested 2-3 years after
   planting.
   COMMON NAMES
   Ipecac, Ipecacuanina, Poaia, Ipecacuanha, Ipecacuana.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: Psychotria ipecacuanha. Ipecac is native of humid,
   tropical regions of Brazil. Yields of 500-600 kg/ha of dried roots have
   been obtained.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
